# Next.js Web App Conventions

## Stack

- **Framework**: Next.js 16 App Router, React 19
- **UI**: HeroUI (`@heroui/react`), Tailwind CSS 4 (`@tailwindcss/postcss`)
- **i18n**: next-intl — strings in `src/i18n/locales/{en,zh}.json`; locale via `locale` cookie (not URL prefix)
- **Guide**: MDX in `src/content/{en,zh}/`; search index via `pnpm generate:md`
- **API**: `src/utils/request.ts` + thin clients in `src/api/`; domain logic in `src/modules/`
- **Auth**: JWT in HTTP-only cookie `retentio_token`
- **Validation**: Zod schemas in `src/modules/*/`

## File organization

```
src/
├── app/              # App Router layouts and pages
├── components/       # UI by area (app/, auth/, decks/, facts/, layout/, guide/)
├── modules/          # Domain: actions, services, schemas
├── api/              # HTTP client wrappers
├── hooks/
├── lib/              # logger, locale, token helpers
├── i18n/
├── content/          # MDX guide sources
└── utils/            # request.ts, shared helpers
```

## Patterns

- Prefer **Server Components** by default; add `"use client"` only when needed (hooks, browser APIs, interactivity).
- Server actions and services live under `src/modules/<domain>/`.
- Use shared `AppButton`, `AppInput`, etc. from `src/components/app/` — match existing HeroUI usage.
- All user-visible strings through next-intl — update **both** `en.json` and `zh.json`.
- Do not edit generated `public/search-index/` — run `pnpm generate:md` after MDX changes.

## Checks before commit

```bash
pnpm lint:ci
pnpm test
pnpm build
```

E2E (when auth flows change): `pnpm test:e2e`
